#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1345(list_entry:short_description|value:smoke)
msgid ""
"A Finnish-style hot sauna in which the stove has no chimney but instead the "
"smoke fills the room when the sauna is prepared, and the smoke is then "
"ventilated out when the sauna is ready."
msgstr "フィンランド式の高温サウナで、ストーブには煙突が無く、準備中には部屋が煙で満たされており、煙はサウナの準備ができたら換気されます。 "

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1341(list_entry:short_description|value:hot)
msgid ""
"A Finnish-style sauna with a temperature of over 60°C because of the water "
"thrown on the rocks of the stove. This kind of sauna is relatively dry "
"because of the high temperature."
msgstr "フィンランド式のサウナで、ストーブの周囲の岩に掛けた水によって60度を超える温度です。この種のサウナは高温のため、比較的乾燥しています。 "

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5069(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:harbour)
msgid ""
"A Harbour installation with a service or commercial operation of public "
"interest. A body of water providing protection for vessels, and providing "
"anchoring and docking facilities."
msgstr "公益性のあるサービスないし営業的な運営を行う港湾施設。船舶の保護や、投錨・停泊施設を提供する水域。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1346(list_entry:short_description|value:hanjeungmak)
msgid ""
"A Korean-style hot and dry sauna, in which water is not thrown on the stove."
msgstr "韓国式の高温乾燥サウナで、その中ではストーブに水が掛けられることはありません。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:6974(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Guidepost)
msgid ""
"A Signpost/Guidepost to indicate the directions to different destinations."
msgstr "それぞれの目的地の方向を示す道標。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1342(list_entry:short_description|value:steam)
msgid ""
"A Turkish-style steam sauna with a lower temperature and limited visibility "
"because of the steam generated."
msgstr "トルコ式のスチームサウナです。温度は低めで、蒸気のために視界はよくありません。 "

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5035(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:beacon_special_purpose)
msgid ""
"A beacon primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which "
"is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to "
"Mariners."
msgstr "主にエリアや特徴を示すために使用されるビーコン。意味は海図、水路誌、水路通報を参照のこと"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5032(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:beacon_isolated_danger)
msgid ""
"A beacon that is moored on or above an isolated danger of limited extent, "
"which has navigable water all around it."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5031(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:beacon_cardinal)
msgid ""
"A beacon used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner "
"may find the best navigable water."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5034(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:beacon_safe_water)
msgid ""
"A beacon used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5033(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:beacon_lateral)
msgid ""
"A beacon used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be"
" followed."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:6944(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Map)
msgid "A board with a map."
msgstr "地図のある掲示板"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:6963(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Information_Board)
msgid "A board with information."
msgstr "情報の掲示板"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5076(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:light_float)
msgid ""
"A boat-like structure used instead of a light buoy in waters where strong "
"streams or currents are experienced, or when a greater elevation than that "
"of a light buoy is necessary."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:4735(label:text|group:Water|preset:Other_waterbodies)
msgid "A body of water, such as a lake or pond."
msgstr "湖や池などの水域のことです。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5045(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_special_purpose)
msgid ""
"A buoy primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is"
" apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notices to "
"Mariners."
msgstr "主にエリアや特徴を示すために使用されるブイ。意味は海図、水路誌、水路通報を参照のこと"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5042(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_isolated_danger)
msgid ""
"A buoy that is moored on or above an isolated danger of limited extent, "
"which has navigable water all around it."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5041(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_installation)
msgid "A buoy used for loading tankers with gas or oil."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5040(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_cardinal)
msgid ""
"A buoy used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where the mariner "
"may find the best navigable water."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5044(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_safe_water)
msgid "A buoy used to indicate that there is navigable water around the mark."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5043(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:buoy_lateral)
msgid ""
"A buoy used to indicate the port or starboard hand side of the route to be "
"followed."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5121(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:topmark)
msgid ""
"A characteristic shape secured at the top of a buoy or beacon to aid in its "
"identification."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5130(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:rock)
msgid ""
"A concreted mass of stony material or coral which dries, is awash or is "
"below the water surface."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5092(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:pipeline_submarine)
msgid ""
"A connected set of pipes for conveying liquids, slurries, or gases. A "
"pipeline lying on or buried under the seabed or the land."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5085(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:oil_barrier)
msgid "A construction to dam oil flow on water."
msgstr "水上の油の流出を防ぐための構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5123(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:separation_crossing)
msgid "A defined area where traffic lanes cross."
msgstr "交通車線が交差する、明確に区切られた区域。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5030(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:anchor_berth)
msgid ""
"A designated area of water where a single vessel, sea plane etc. may anchor."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5113(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:seaplane_landing_area)
msgid ""
"A designated portion of water for the landing and take-off of sea-planes."
msgstr "水上飛行機の離着陸のために指定された水域。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5098(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:radar_reflector)
msgid "A device capable of, or intended for, reflecting radar signals."
msgstr "レーダー信号を反射する能力を持つ、または反射することを目的とした装置。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5056(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:distance_mark)
msgid ""
"A distance mark indicates the distance measured from an origin and consists "
"of either a solid visible structure or a distinct location without special "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5077(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:light_vessel)
msgid ""
"A distinctively marked vessel anchored or moored at a charted point, to "
"serve as an important floating aid to navigation with major light."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14324(label:text|group:Places|preset:Farm)
msgid "A farm within a bigger settlement"
msgstr "大きな集落の中にある農場"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:2116(check:text|key:kids_area:fee)
msgid "A fee must be paid"
msgstr "有料"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5115(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:shoreline_construction)
msgid ""
"A fixed artificial structure in the water and/or adjoining the land. It may "
"also refer to features such as training walls, which are not necessarily "
"connected to, nor form part of the shoreline."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:4809(label:text|group:Water|preset:Beach)
msgid "A flat area of sand, gravel or pebble next to water."
msgstr "水際にある、砂、砂利、丸石の平坦な領域です。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5093(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:pontoon)
msgid ""
"A floating structure, usually rectangular in shape which serves as landing, "
"pier head or bridge support."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5111(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:sea_area)
msgid ""
"A geographically defined part of the sea or other navigable waters. It may "
"be specified within its limits by its proper name."
msgstr "海またはその他の航行可能な水域のうち、地理的に区切られた領域。その領域内は、固有名詞によって特定される場合がある。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:12493(list_entry:short_description|group:Historic_Places_&_Objects|preset:Fortification_Site|value:battery)
msgid "A group of artillary (cannon) in a fixed fortification"
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5338(label:text|group:Railway|preset:Railway_junction)
msgid "A junction where railways diverge or converge."
msgstr "鉄道が分岐または合流する地点。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:2112(check:text|key:kids_area)
msgid "A kids area is available"
msgstr "あり"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5120(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:submarine_transit_lane)
msgid "A lane where submarines may navigate under water or at the surface."
msgstr "潜水艦が水中または水上を航行できる航路。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5109(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:sand_waves)
msgid ""
"A large mobile wave-like sediment feature in shallow water and composed of "
"sand. The wavelength may reach 100 metres, the amplitude may be up to 20 "
"metres."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5114(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:tank)
msgid ""
"A large storage structure used for storing loose materials, liquids and/or "
"gases."
msgstr "ばら積み物、液体、および／または気体を貯蔵するために使用される大型の貯蔵施設。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14569(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Tree_Row)
msgid "A line of trees."
msgstr "木の列です。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5125(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:separation_line)
msgid ""
"A line separating the lanes in which ships are proceeding in opposite, or "
"nearly opposite directions; or separating a traffic lane from an adjacent "
"sea area; or separating traffic lanes designated for particular classes of "
"ships proceeding in the same direction."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5078(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:lock_basin)
msgid ""
"A lock basin is a wet dock in a waterway, permitting a ship to pass from one"
" level to another."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5089(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:pile)
msgid ""
"A long heavy timber or section of steel, wood, concrete, etc. forced into "
"the earth which may serve as a support, as for a pier, or a free standing "
"pole within a marine environment."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14421(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Valley)
msgid "A low area between hills."
msgstr "丘の間の低い領域です。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5075(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:light_minor)
msgid ""
"A luminous or lighted aid to navigation, light. The IALA Maritime Buoyage "
"System rules (INT-1 Q 130) will apply to minor lights, but not to leading "
"lights."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5073(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:light)
msgid ""
"A luminous or lighted aid to navigation. Light. Lighthouse. An all around "
"light is a light that is visible over the whole horizon of interest to "
"marine navigation. Secotr lights present different appearances (in "
"particular, different colours) over various parts of the horizon of interest"
" to maritime navigation."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5053(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:crane)
msgid ""
"A machine for lifting, shifting and lowering objects or materials by means "
"of a swinging boom or with a lifting apparatus."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5062(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:wall)
msgid "A man-made barrier used as an enclosure or boundary or for protection."
msgstr "囲いや境界、あるいは保護のために使用される人工の障壁。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:7059(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Route_marker)
msgid "A marker along a route."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5108(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:retro_reflector)
msgid ""
"A means of distinguishing unlighted marks at night. Retro-reflective "
"material is secured to the mark in a particular pattern to reflect back "
"light."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14411(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Ridge)
msgid "A mountain or hill ridge."
msgstr "山や丘の尾根。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5036(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:berth)
msgid "A named or numbered place where a vessel is moored at a wharf."
msgstr "埠頭において、船舶が係留される、名称または番号が付けられた場所。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5119(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:spring)
msgid ""
"A natural issue of water or other substances from the earth. One on the "
"bottom of the sea is called a 'submarine spring'."
msgstr "地中から自然に湧き出る水やその他の物質。海底にあるものは「海底泉」と呼ばれる。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1344(list_entry:short_description|value:dry)
msgid "A non-steam dry sauna in which water is not thrown on the stove."
msgstr "蒸気を使わないドライサウナで、ストーブに水をかけることはありません。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14738(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Rock)
msgid ""
"A notable rock or group of rocks, with at least one of them firmly attached "
"to the underlying bedrock."
msgstr "目立つ岩、または岩群で、少なくとも1つは下層の岩盤にしっかりと付着しているもの。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5083(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:notice)
msgid ""
"A notice board or sign indicating information to the mariner. A signboard "
"used to indicate prohibitions, regulations, restrictions, recommendations "
"and general information which apply to a waterway or a section of a "
"waterway."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:3935(label:text|group:Barriers|preset:Wicket_gate)
msgid "A pedestrian door or gate near a larger gate"
msgstr "より大きな門の近くにある歩行者用の扉または門"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5086(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:platform)
msgid ""
"A permanent offshore structure, either fixed or floating, used in the "
"production of oil or natural gas."
msgstr "石油または天然ガスの生産に使用される、固定式または浮体式の恒久的な海洋構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14367(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Glacier)
msgid ""
"A persistent body of dense ice that is constantly moving under its own "
"weight."
msgstr "自身の重みで絶えず移動する、密度の高い氷の塊。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:8764(list_entry:short_description|group:Emergency|preset:Fire_Hydrant|value:wet_barrel)
msgid ""
"A pillar hydrant where the barrel is pressurized at all times, with "
"individual valves for each outlet."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:8763(list_entry:short_description|group:Emergency|preset:Fire_Hydrant|value:dry_barrel)
msgid "A pillar hydrant where the water shutoff valve is below ground."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5118(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:small_craft_facility)
msgid ""
"A place at which a service generally of interest to small craft or pleasure "
"boats is available."
msgstr "小型船舶やレジャーボートにとって一般的に有益なサービスが利用できる場所。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5102(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:radio_station)
msgid "A place equipped to transmit radio waves."
msgstr "電波を送信する設備を備えた場所。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5106(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:rescue_station)
msgid ""
"A place where equipment for saving life at sea is maintained. Also called "
"life saving station."
msgstr "海上での人命救助に必要な装備を整備する場所。救命ステーションとも呼ばれる。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5133(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:vehicle_transfer)
msgid ""
"A place where vehicles can be loaded or unloaded from the inland vessel with"
" onboard or on-shore facilities."
msgstr "船上または岸壁の設備を利用して、内陸水路を航行する船舶への荷物の積み下ろしができる場所。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5054(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:control_point)
msgid ""
"A point on the ground where position (horizontal and vertical) is used as a "
"base for a dependent survey. Also referred to as a control station."
msgstr "地上の測量における基準点（水平方向および垂直方向の位置）として用いられる地点。基準点とも呼ばれる。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:4584(label:text|group:Water|preset:Spring)
msgid ""
"A point where groundwater naturally flows to the surface of the earth from "
"underground."
msgstr "地下水が自然に地表に湧き出る地点。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5072(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:landmark)
msgid ""
"A prominent object at a fixed location which can be used in determining a "
"location or a direction."
msgstr "特定の場所に固定された目印となる物体で、位置や方向を特定するために利用できるもの。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:4836(label:text|group:Water|preset:Cape)
msgid ""
"A prominent, elevated piece of land sticking out into the sea or large lake."
msgstr "海や大きな湖に突き出た、目立つ高台の土地。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5049(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:causeway)
msgid "A raised way across low or wet ground or water."
msgstr "低い地面や湿地、あるいは水面を横切るように作られた、一段高い通路。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5103(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:recommended_route_centreline)
msgid ""
"A recommended route centerline indicates the 'centerline' of a recommended "
"route (often marked by centerline buoys)."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5110(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:seabed_area)
msgid ""
"A region of the seabed including the material of which it is composed and "
"its physical characteristics. Also called nature of bottom, character (or "
"characteristics) of the bottom, or quality of the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5039(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:building)
msgid ""
"A relatively permanent structure, roofed and usually walled. It is designed "
"for some particular use which it may be important to indicate."
msgstr "比較的恒久的な構造物で、屋根があり、通常は壁で囲まれている。特定の用途のために設計されており、その用途を明記することが重要である場合がある。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14492(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Arch)
msgid "A rock arch naturally formed by erosion, with an opening underneath."
msgstr "浸食によって自然に形成された岩のアーチで、下部に開口部がある。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5061(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:ferry_route)
msgid ""
"A route in a body of water where a ferry crosses from one shoreline to "
"another."
msgstr "フェリーが一方の岸からもう一方の岸へと渡る、水域内の航路。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5104(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:recommended_track)
msgid ""
"A route which has been specially examined to ensure so far as possible that "
"it is free of dangers and along which ships are advised to navigate. That "
"portion of a 'navigation line' that a ship should use for navigation."
msgstr "危険が可能な限り排除されていることを確認するために特別に調査された航路であり、船舶が航行するよう推奨されている航路。船舶が航行に使用すべき「航路」の一部。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5126(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:separation_roundabout)
msgid ""
"A routeing measure comprising a separation point or circular separation zone"
" and a circular traffic lane within defined limits. Traffic within the "
"roundabout is separated by moving in a counter clockwise direction around "
"the separation point or zone."
msgstr "分離点または円形の分離ゾーンと、所定の範囲内に設けられた円形の車線からなる交通誘導措置。ロータリー内の交通は、分離点または分離ゾーンを反時計回りに周回することで分離される。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5094(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:precautionary_area)
msgid ""
"A routeing measure comprising an area within defined limits where ships must"
" navigate with particular caution and within which the direction of traffic "
"flow may be recommended."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5071(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:inshore_traffic_zone)
msgid ""
"A routing measure comprising a designated area between the landward boundary"
" of a traffic separation scheme and the adjacent coast, to be used in "
"accordance with the provisions of the International Regulations for "
"Preventing Collisions at Sea."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14358(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Saddle)
msgid "A saddle point between mountains or hills."
msgstr "山や丘の間の鞍部。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1339(list_entry:short_description|value:yes)
msgid "A sauna is available but its type is not specified."
msgstr "サウナが有効ですが、種類が指定されていません。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1340(list_entry:short_description|value:no)
msgid "A sauna is not available."
msgstr "このサウナは利用できません。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1347(list_entry:short_description|value:aroma)
msgid ""
"A sauna that constantly has an aroma, NOT a Finnish sauna with occasional "
"aroma liquid added to the water."
msgstr "常に香りが漂っているサウナ。水に時折アロマ液を加えるフィンランド式サウナとは異なる。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:1343(list_entry:short_description|value:infrared)
msgid "A sauna-like construction that is used for infrared therapy."
msgstr "赤外線療法に用いられる、サウナのような構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5058(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:dumping_ground)
msgid ""
"A sea area where dredged material or other potentially more harmful "
"material, e.g. explosives, chemical waste, is deliberately deposited."
msgstr "浚渫土砂や、爆発物、化学廃棄物など、より有害な可能性のある物質が意図的に投棄される海域。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14430(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Mountain_range)
msgid ""
"A series of high ridges and mountain peaks ranged in a line and connected by"
" high ground."
msgstr "一連の高い尾根や山々が一列に連なり、高台によってつながっている場所。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14749(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Stone)
msgid ""
"A single notable free-standing rock, which may differ from the composition "
"of the terrain it lies in."
msgstr "周囲の地形の構成とは異なる、目立つ独立した岩石。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14590(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Shrub)
msgid "A single shrub."
msgstr "単一の低木。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14541(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Tree)
msgid "A single tree."
msgstr "単一の木。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:12488(list_entry:short_description|group:Historic_Places_&_Objects|preset:Fortification_Site|value:sconce)
msgid "A small protective fortification"
msgstr "小さな防御要塞"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5107(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:restricted_area)
msgid ""
"A specified area on land or water designated by an appropriate authority "
"within which access or navigation is restricted in accordance with certain "
"specified conditions."
msgstr "適切な当局によって指定された、陸上または水上の特定区域であり、その区域内では、特定の条件に従って立ち入りまたは航行が制限される。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5100(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:radar_station)
msgid ""
"A station with a transmitter emitting pulses of ultra-high frequency radio "
"waves which are reflected by solid objects and are detected upon their "
"return to the sending station."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5038(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:bunker_station)
msgid "A station, at which a ship is able to bunker fuel, water or ballast."
msgstr "船舶が燃料、水、またはバラストを補給できるステーション。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14458(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Earth_bank)
msgid ""
"A steep earth bank, with a significant vertical, or near vertical (leave the"
" lower face to the right of the way)."
msgstr "急勾配の土手。かなり垂直、もしくはほぼ垂直（下側の斜面は右側に残す）。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14438(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Cliff)
msgid ""
"A steep rock face exposure, with a significant vertical, or near vertical "
"(leave the lower face to the right of the way)."
msgstr "急峻な岩壁の区間。かなり垂直、もしくはほぼ垂直（下側の斜面は右側に残す）。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5082(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:navigation_line)
msgid ""
"A straight line extending towards an area of navigational interest and "
"generally generated by two navigational aids or one navigational aid and a "
"bearing."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5037(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:bridge)
msgid ""
"A structure erected over a body of water, railroad, etc. to provide a "
"roadway for vehicles, pedestrians or to carry utility services."
msgstr "水域や鉄道などの上に建設され、車両や歩行者のための通路を提供したり、公共サービスを提供したりする構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5065(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:fishing_facility)
msgid ""
"A structure in shallow water for fishing purposes which can be an "
"obstruction to ships in general."
msgstr "浅瀬に設置された漁業用の構造物で、一般的に船舶の航行の妨げとなる可能性がある。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5067(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:gridiron)
msgid ""
"A structure in the intertidal zone serving as a support for vessels at low "
"stages of the tide to permit work on the exposed portion of the vessel's "
"hull."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5064(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:fortified_structure)
msgid ""
"A structure that is specifically designed or reinforced to provide for "
"defence from armed attack."
msgstr "武装攻撃からの防御を目的として特別に設計または強化された構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5066(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:gate)
msgid ""
"A structure that may be swung, drawn, or lowered to block an entrance or "
"passageway."
msgstr "入り口や通路を塞ぐために、振り下ろしたり、引き出したり、下げたりすることができる構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:6953(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Tactile_map)
msgid "A tactile map."
msgstr "触地図。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:7041(label:text|group:Tourism|preset:Tactile_model)
msgid "A tactile model."
msgstr "触覚模型。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5105(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:recommended_traffic_lane)
msgid ""
"A traffic flow pattern indicating a recommended directional movement of "
"traffic where it is impractical or unnecessary to adopt an established "
"direction of traffic flow. Indicates the recommended traffic flow e.g., "
"between two TSS, in the entrance areas of a TSS, beside a deep water route."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5116(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:signal_station_traffic)
msgid ""
"A traffic signal station is a place on shore from which signals are made to "
"regulate the movement of traffic."
msgstr "交通信号所とは、交通の流れを規制するための信号を発信する、陸上にある場所のことです。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5099(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:radar_transponder)
msgid ""
"A transponder beacon transmitting a coded signal on radar frequency, "
"permitting an interrogating craft to determine the bearing and range of the "
"transponder. Also called racon."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14583(label:text|group:Nature|preset:Tree_Stump)
msgid "A tree stump."
msgstr "木の切り株。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5095(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:pylon)
msgid ""
"A vertical construction consisting, for example, of a steel framework or "
"pre-stressed concrete to carry cables, a bridge, etc."
msgstr "ケーブルや橋などを支えるための鉄骨構造やプレストレストコンクリートからなる垂直構造物。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:14376(label:text|group:Geography|preset:Volcano)
msgid "A volcano, either dormant, extinct or active."
msgstr "休火山、死火山、活火山のいずれか。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5117(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:signal_station_warning)
msgid ""
"A warning signal station is a place on shore from which warning signals are "
"made to ships at sea."
msgstr "警報信号所とは、陸上にある場所から、海上を航行する船舶に向けて警報信号を発信する場所のことです。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5063(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:fog_signal)
msgid ""
"A warning signal transmitted by a vessel, or aid to navigation, during "
"periods of low visibility."
msgstr "視界不良時に船舶または航行援助施設が発信する警告信号。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:8744(list_entry:short_description|group:Emergency|preset:Fire_Hydrant|value:groundwater)
msgid "A water well."
msgstr "井戸。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5135(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:waterway_gauge)
msgid "A waterway gauge is an instrument for measuring water levels."
msgstr "水路水位計は、水位を測定するための機器です。"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5127(list_entry:short_description|group:Shipping|preset:Seamark|value:separation_zone)
msgid ""
"A zone separating the lanes in which ships are proceeding in opposite or "
"nearly opposite directions; or separating a traffic lane from an adjacent "
"sea area; or separating traffic lanes designated for particular classes of "
"ships proceeding in the same direction."
msgstr ""

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:11606(multiselect:display_values|group:Man_Made|preset:Surveillance|key:surveillance:type)
msgid "ALPR"
msgstr "ALPR"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:2821(list_entry:display_value|group:Lane_attributes|preset:Single_direction_roads|value:abandoned)
#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:2859(list_entry:display_value|group:Lane_attributes|preset:Bi-directional_roads|value:abandoned)
#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:2891(list_entry:display_value|group:Lane_attributes|preset:Bi-directional_roads|value:abandoned)
#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:357(list_entry:display_value|value:abandoned)
msgid "Abandoned"
msgstr "放棄"

#: C:\Users\simon\git\beautified-JOSM-preset\build\temp/v4.xml:5256(item:name|group:Railway|preset:Abandoned_Rail)
